            "description": "<p>We are looking for a Digital Marketing Intern to support our online marketing activities across Google Ads, Meta Ads, SEO/content, and social media. You will work directly with a senior digital marketing specialist, assist in marketing planning, and bring creative ideas to our campaigns.</p>\n<p>You’ll be working across a couple of brands within our group, gaining exposure to different audiences and campaigns. For administrative purposes, the internship will be registered under CV Wisma Kencana Andalas.</p><p>\n<strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>\n</p>\n\n<ul><li>Support further marketing planning for the company, including brainstorming campaign ideas, contributing to simple strategy outlines, and helping prepare basic planning documents.</li>\n  <li>Support weekly and monthly Google Ads performance reporting, document campaign findings and assist in preparing presentations for internal stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Conduct weekly Google Ads search term analysis, flag irrelevant queries and new keyword opportunities.</li>\n  <li>Review Google Ads copy and creative assets for performance and suggest improvements where applicable.</li>\n  <li>Assist in keyword research and content gap analysis for SEO planning and help develop outlines for travel-related articles.</li>\n  <li>Support basic research and fact-checking for travel-related articles.</li>\n  <li>Proactively research trends and think strategically to develop content ideas, directions, and captions of Social Media, while supporting content planning, scheduling, and publishing</li>\n  <li>Work under the guidance of the Senior Digital Marketing Specialist for execution, while being expected to take initiative in developing and improving social media without waiting for direction</li>\n  <li>Assist in further marketing planning for the company, including brainstorming ideas, outlining simple strategies, and helping prepare basic planning documents.</li>\n  <li>Use AI tools (Perplexity / Claude) to speed up research, idea generation, and drafts, while learning how to review and improve AI-generated output.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What We Are Looking For</strong>\n</p>\n\n<ul><li>Final-year student or fresh graduate in Marketing, Communications, Business, or a related field, available to commit full-time for the internship period.</li>\n  <li>Strong interest in digital marketing and branding, with a more creative mindset than purely data-driven.</li>\n  <li>Comfortable working with basic performance metrics, reports, and dashboards.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented and responsible, able to follow guidelines while suggesting new ideas and creative angles.</li>\n  <li>Good written communication skills in English.</li>\n  <li>Curious and willing to work with AI tools (e.g., Claude, Perplexity) as part of the daily workflow; prior experience beyond basic prompting is a plus.</li>\n  <li>Basic familiarity with at least one platform (Google Ads, Meta Business Suite, or SEO tools) is a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What You Will Gain</strong>\n</p>\n\n<ul><li>Hands-on experience across Google Ads and Meta Ads with real budgets, SEO, and social media.</li>\n  <li>Practical experience using AI tools as part of a real marketing workflow, working alongside AI to produce better and more efficient outputs.</li>\n  <li>Direct day-to-day guidance from a senior digital marketing specialist across all channels.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br></p>",
