            "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Partner with cross-functional stakeholders (product, marketing, content, revenue) to translate business questions into analytical frameworks and deliverables</li>\n  <li>Build and maintain dashboards, reports, and self-serve analytics tools that support day-to-day decisions</li>\n  <li>Conduct deep-dive analyses to surface trends, opportunities, and risks across engagement, monetization, audience growth, and content performance</li>\n  <li>Design and analyze experiments (A/B tests, feature rollouts) to validate hypotheses and quantify business impact</li>\n  <li>Develop forecasting and quantitative models to support both short-term planning and long-term strategy</li>\n  <li>Define and standardize key metrics across teams, ensuring consistency in how the business measures success</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with Data Engineering on data quality, modeling, and pipeline improvements</li>\n  <li>Mentor junior analysts and champion data literacy and a data-driven culture across the organization</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>3+ years of experience in business analytics, BI, or data analytics roles (media, digital, or consumer tech industries strongly preferred)</li>\n  <li>Strong proficiency in SQL — comfortable writing complex queries, optimizing performance, and working with large datasets in cloud data warehouses (BigQuery, Snowflake, Redshift, or similar)</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with modern BI/visualization tools (Looker, Tableau, Power BI, Metabase, or similar)</li>\n  <li>Working knowledge of Python (or R) for analysis, automation, and statistical modeling</li>\n  <li>Solid grasp of statistics, experimentation methodology, and forecasting techniques</li>\n  <li>Strong business acumen with deep understanding of media industry metrics (DAU/MAU, retention, ARPU, CTR, watch time, ad revenue metrics, etc.)</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills — able to translate complex analyses into clear narratives for both technical and non-technical audiences</li>\n  <li>Self-driven, comfortable with ambiguity, and able to manage multiple priorities under tight deadlines</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Nice to Have:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Familiarity with data modeling concepts and tools like dbt</li>\n  <li>Experience with version control (Git) and code-based analytics workflows</li>\n  <li>Exposure to machine learning or predictive modeling</li>\n  <li>Prior experience mentoring analysts or leading analytics projects end-to-end</li>\n</ul>",
